latestIgtvVideos.title: Regrets of people on death bed
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I came across this video on Whtsapp (no sources identified for credits), but felt every word of it. I don't want to die with these regrets. 
Learning to stay positive, happy and live life per my terms everyday.
My regret so far: I didn't enjoy my life in 20's and put in so much of energy in the worthless job where people are treated as puppets and not humans. 
Regret 2: As mentioned in video, I was so concerned about what people will think/say about me if I do this or that (as mentioned in as regret no1 in this video).
I have changed alot as a person now over the past 3-4 years and still exploring and learning new things everyday. Hope you connect with this video which I felt sharing❤️

Do let me know what is your biggest regret (in comments or DM), either ways you like ?
